description:
&lt;p&gt;Fleet community nursing team are looking to recruit a Community Sister/charge nurse into their dynamic, forward thinking team. We deliver complex care to people in their own homes and facilitate the best possible care ensuring people are provided with the care they require, where they require it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have a team of highly skilled community nurses as well as competent and supportive nursing associate, associate practitioner and health care assistants. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you would like a different challenge in the Community and aspire to change how nursing is currently delivered then this role may be for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer extensive further CPD training and inhouse training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is for a full time experienced nurse, this will be a mixture of day and night shifts, working a variety of different patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drivers licence and access to a vehicle is essential - please read full list of Person Specifics. Informal contact is encouraged and visits are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lucas, llucas@nhs.net, 07919175592&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note Lynda Lucas works part-time and will respond on her return to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An alternative contact is Kelly Gray, Team Lead Rushmoor, 07557926032 , kellygray@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
